<h2>Conversion rate benchmarks for Google Ads</h2>
<p><strong>The <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/2025-google-ads-benchmarks" target="_blank" rel="noopener">average conversion rate across Google Ads</a> is 7.52%.¬†</strong></p>
<div style="text-align: center;"></div>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-GA-Benchmarks-CVR-871x1024.webp" alt="2025 google ads benchmarks - conversion rate chart year over year" width="871" height="1024" class="aligncenter wp-image-91513 size-large" /></div>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2734.png" alt="‚ú¥" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Note: </strong>We update this data regularly! <strong><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/google-ads-industry-benchmarks?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_2025GoogleAdsBenchmarks_Download">Download the PDF of our latest Google Ads Benchmarks report here</a>.</strong></p>
<p>What&#8217;s interesting is the change in these conversion rate benchmarks over the years. The last time we calculated average Google Ads conversion rates, we found a benchmark of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/2024-google-ads-benchmarks" target="_blank" rel="noopener">6.96%</a>. So, Google Ads average CVR across all industries has actually increased by 6.84% year over year.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-GA-Benchmarks-YOY-1024x602.webp" alt="google ads benchmarks - overall changes year over year" width="1024" height="602" class="aligncenter wp-image-91520 size-large" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-GA-Benchmarks-YOY-980x577.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-GA-Benchmarks-YOY-480x282.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></p>
