<div id="average-facebook-ads-cost-per-conversion-by-industry"></div>
<h2>How much does a Facebook Ads conversion cost?</h2>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>The average cost per conversion across Facebook Ads is $27.66.</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-fb-benchmarks-cpl-leads-866x1024.webp" alt="2025 facebook ads benchmarks - average cost per lead chart" width="866" height="1024" class="aligncenter wp-image-93942 size-large" /></p>
<p>You&#8217;ll find that most industries tend to have their Meta Ads CPLs average out lower than their Google Ads CPLs. For example, the average Education advertiser can expect to cough up just over $90 for each conversion on the Google search network. For each Facebook conversion, however, the average cost is under $29! Of course, the conversions you drive with your search ads may tend to be more valuable than the conversions you drive with <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/how-to-advertise-on-facebook" target="_blank" rel="noopener">your Facebook ads</a>. Nonetheless, if you‚Äôre in Restaurants and Food ($3.16), Real Estate ($16.61), and Career and Employment ($17.64), make sure you‚Äôre taking advantage of your ability to drive cheap high-funnel conversions on Facebook.</p>
<p>It‚Äôs not totally surprising that advertisers in the Dentists and Dental Services ($76.71), Health and Fitness ($52.98), and Beauty and Personal Care ($51.42) industries are investing good amounts of money in each Facebook conversion. Typically, when someone needs a dental solution, they‚Äôre turning to Google search. Meanwhile, health and fitness, as well as beauty and personal care ads, can be extremely competitive across Meta platforms. To be clear, however, that doesn‚Äôt mean you should overlook the value of using Facebook to spread and maintain brand awareness.</p>
