										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Google‚Äôs reach may extend across the world, but for some local searches, we need a trusted solution in our own neighborhood (and quickly)!</p>
<p>Searchers watching their sinks overflow can‚Äôt wait for a plumber from across state lines, and they‚Äôre hesitant to call a stranger to help them get into their car when they‚Äôre locked outside in the middle of the night.</p>
<p>Local service advertisers often struggle to convert these searchers with just SEO or standard search ads alone.</p>
<p>Luckily, Google‚Äôs Local Services Ads (LSAs) can come to the rescue. In this article, we&#8217;re covering everything you need to know about LSAs to make the most of them for your business.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#definition">What are Google Local Services Ads?</a></li>
<li><a href="#industries">What businesses can run Google LSAs?</a></li>
<li><a href="#benefits">Google Local Services Ads benefits</a></li>
<li><a href="#howto">How to get started with Google LSAs</a></li>
<li><a href="#tips">Tips for effective Local Services Ads</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="definition"></div>
<h2>What are Google Local Services Ads?</h2>
<p><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/local-services-ads/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Local Services Ads</a> allow service-based businesses to run ads meant to generate leads directly on the search results page. Rather than linking to a landing page like traditional Google Ads, LSAs are meant to drive calls, form fills, messages, or appointment bookings directly from the ad. Specific industries such as locksmiths, plumbers, garage door professionals, electricians, lawyers, real estate agents, and many more can take advantage of this Google Ads type.</p>
<p>When a searcher enters a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/12/01/google-local-search-trends">local search</a> query, they may see several trusted professionals in their area positioned right above the traditional paid search ads; these ads show a business number, hours, ratings, and reviews.</p>
<p>For example, an LSA might look like this:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-248583 size-full" src="https://localiq.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/google-local-services-ad-verified-badge-ad-example-png-e1760120783229.webp" alt="google local services ad - screenshot of lsa with verified badge example" width="512" height="684" /></p>
<p>Upon clicking on a local advertiser‚Äôs listing, Google prompts them to confirm the job they‚Äôre looking for as well as their service area. If you fit the job and serve that area, you‚Äôll be matched to the searcher, and they‚Äôll be able to review your qualifications, ratings, and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/09/16/get-more-google-reviews">Google reviews</a> before contacting you.</p>
<p>If you‚Äôre <em>not</em> a good fit for their job or you don‚Äôt serve their region, then Google will save you the costs and burdens and will connect them to a more appropriate Local Services Ad.</p>
<p>Google‚Äôs Local Services Ads display on desktop, tablet, and mobile searches; they also have reach beyond traditional search ads.</p>
<p>Local Services Ads are featured in the Google Assistant‚Äôs response to relevant <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/03/14/google-voice-search">voice search</a> queries! The Google Assistant inquires about the searcher‚Äôs job type and location to ensure a quality match for the advertiser.</p>
<p><strong><span data-contrast="auto" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" class="TextRun SCXW153089153 BCX0"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW153089153 BCX0"><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6a8.png" alt="üö®" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> </span></span>Are you making the most of Google Ads?</strong> Find out using our free<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Google Ads Grader</a> tool!</p>
<div id="industries"></div>
<h2>Local Services Ads industries</h2>
<p>Local Service Ads are a dream come true for some industries. Today, Google fully supports Local Services Ads all across the United States for <a href="https://blog.google/outreach-initiatives/small-business/local-services-ads-expands/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">more than 70 industries</a>, including:</p>
<p class="p1"><div class='one_half'>
					<ul>
<li>Appliance repair</li>
<li>Carpenter</li>
<li>Carpet cleaning</li>
<li>Cleaning service</li>
